## Self-Hosted Setup

You're running EnvHaven **self-hosted**. Configure access as needed.

### SSH Access

Configure these environment variables for correct connection strings in the UI:

| Variable | Example | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `ENVHAVEN_SSH_HOST` | `myserver.com` | External hostname |
| `ENVHAVEN_SSH_PORT` | `2222` | External SSH port (default: 2222) |

**SSH command:** `ssh abc@<host> -p 2222`

**Haven CLI:** `haven connect . abc@<host>:2222`

### Exposing Ports

Map container ports in your `docker-compose.yml`:

```yaml
ports:
  - "8443:8443"   # Web IDE
  - "2222:22"     # SSH
  - "3000:3000"   # App dev server (optional)
```

### Starting Dev Servers (Self-Hosted)

When starting a dev server, remind the user to ensure the port is mapped in `docker-compose.yml`:

```yaml
ports:
  - "3000:3000"   # Map your app's port
```

Then access at `http://<your-host>:3000`

### Cloudflare Tunnels (Optional)

`cloudflared` is included. Set `CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN` to enable automatic tunnel.

### Password Authentication

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `PASSWORD` | Web GUI password |
| `SUDO_PASSWORD` | SSH and sudo password |

See [docs/configuration.md](https://github.com/envhaven/envhaven/blob/master/docs/configuration.md) for full configuration reference.

